Hey Adam, I've got an obscure bug for you! We have found a work around for this but we thought it was worth bringing to you attention.

It seems prefab changes are not applied on the main thread when the plugins are reloaded. If one of the properties being set by the prefab causes a texture to be loaded it then OpenGL throws exceptions since the calls did not come from the main thread.

To reproduce this, create a GameObject with the following Test component and save it as a prefab. If you then cause the scene to be reloaded by rebuilding your core plugin you should get a series of OpenGL errors. You will need to replace GameRes.Data.SomeTexture with a non default texture, since the defaults are loaded by Duality on startup.

```
[Serializable]
    public class Test : Component
    {
        private int _number;

        public int Number
        {
            get { return _number; }
            set
            {
                _number = value;
                var texture = GameRes.Data.SomeTexture;
                var width = texture.PixelWidth;
            }
        }

        protected override void OnCopyTo(Component target, CloneProvider provider)
        {
            base.OnCopyTo(target, provider);

            var clone = target as Test;

            if (clone == null)
            {
                return;
            }

            clone.Number = Number;
        }
    }
```
